WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:45.400


00:00:54.796 --> 00:00:57.963
YUMI'S CELLS 3

00:00:58.963 --> 00:01:02.963
EPISODE 16
THE PRETTY OLDER GIRL WHO BUYS MEALS

00:01:29.546 --> 00:01:32.255
THE BRAIN SCIENCE OF LOVE
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN FALLING IN LOVE

00:02:01.130 --> 00:02:02.922
MS. KIM, PLEASE CALL ME WHEN YOU WAKE UP

00:02:05.005 --> 00:02:06.172
It's nine already?

00:02:10.505 --> 00:02:12.172
Oh, Ms. Kim.

00:02:12.671 --> 00:02:14.130
Hello, Na-hee.

00:02:14.214 --> 00:02:15.755
Oh no. Did I wake you up?

00:02:16.130 --> 00:02:17.922
No, I was already up.

00:02:18.963 --> 00:02:21.421
- Already?
- Yeah, why?

00:02:23.047 --> 00:02:25.297
I was wondering when's a good time
for our meeting next week.

00:02:25.379 --> 00:02:27.130
Shin PD was asking.

00:02:28.463 --> 00:02:30.421
He could've just asked me directly.

00:02:31.172 --> 00:02:33.088
He said he didn't want to
disturb your writing.

00:02:33.379 --> 00:02:34.755
I'm making good progress

00:02:34.838 --> 00:02:36.339
so I'll finish episode 15 today.

00:02:37.005 --> 00:02:38.172
Let's have the meeting tomorrow.

00:02:38.255 --> 00:02:39.796
Episode 15 is already done?

00:02:40.005 --> 00:02:41.880
Yeah, I've picked up some speed.

00:02:42.255 --> 00:02:44.255
That's amazing!

00:02:44.963 --> 00:02:46.588
But Ms. Kim, did you pull an all-nighter?

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:48.505
No, I got some sleep.

00:02:48.838 --> 00:02:50.463
Can I help you with anything?

00:02:50.546 --> 00:02:52.255
No, it's the weekend, so just rest.

00:02:52.630 --> 00:02:53.963
I'll let you know if I need you.

00:02:54.047 --> 00:02:55.713
Okay, I understand.

00:02:56.255 --> 00:02:57.505
You got this, Ms. Kim!

00:02:57.671 --> 00:02:58.838
Let's go!

00:03:01.505 --> 00:03:03.379
Why is she making progress
so quickly all of a sudden?

00:03:04.588 --> 00:03:05.755
It's strange.

00:03:09.630 --> 00:03:10.838
What's not to like?

00:03:10.922 --> 00:03:12.214
This is how it should be.

00:03:24.880 --> 00:03:27.130
The village is so peaceful.

00:03:27.379 --> 00:03:30.088
I'm almost grateful to Soon-rok
for drawing the boundary.

00:03:31.005 --> 00:03:33.880
When I think about how we wasted
all those weeks for nothing...

00:03:35.588 --> 00:03:37.588
it really makes my blood boil.

00:03:46.088 --> 00:03:47.130
What's that?

00:03:51.130 --> 00:03:53.047
Hey, what is it?

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:00.755
Hey! What's going on?

00:04:02.338 --> 00:04:03.463
Today is Sunday.

00:04:03.546 --> 00:04:05.296
It's Soon-rok's blind date.

00:04:05.755 --> 00:04:06.880
So what?

00:04:08.172 --> 00:04:09.588
What do we do?

00:04:12.796 --> 00:04:14.130
Who pushed for it?

00:04:14.214 --> 00:04:16.338
Why is she fussing
when she's the one who set it up?

00:04:16.546 --> 00:04:17.922
It's your fault.

00:04:18.338 --> 00:04:20.505
You, Pride!

00:04:22.005 --> 00:04:24.880
Was I supposed to just stand by
while Soon-rok was drawing the line?

00:04:25.130 --> 00:04:26.963
You could've just said you'd look into it.

00:04:27.047 --> 00:04:28.671
Why did you have to actually set it up?

00:04:28.963 --> 00:04:31.005
That's how I protected Yu-mi's pride

00:04:31.088 --> 00:04:32.630
because I actually set it up.

00:04:33.005 --> 00:04:34.172
Thanks to my judgment

00:04:34.254 --> 00:04:36.463
Yu-mi was able to save face.

00:04:36.796 --> 00:04:38.254
Now, don't forget, everyone.

00:04:38.338 --> 00:04:40.421
If you say you don't like me

00:04:40.713 --> 00:04:43.463
then I don't like you either!

00:04:43.755 --> 00:04:45.880
Just shut up!

00:04:49.338 --> 00:04:50.922
Why don't you shut up?

00:04:58.922 --> 00:05:01.463
There are only a few hours left.

00:05:06.838 --> 00:05:08.463
My chest is churning.

00:05:10.922 --> 00:05:12.880
Like something's about to explode.

00:05:12.963 --> 00:05:15.838
That kind of simmering feeling?

00:05:17.505 --> 00:05:18.630
What's wrong with her?

00:05:23.088 --> 00:05:24.338
Love is acting weird.

00:05:24.671 --> 00:05:26.379
I think she's about to explode!

00:05:28.338 --> 00:05:30.213
Hey, don't come over here!

00:05:31.005 --> 00:05:32.005
What a sight.

00:05:32.213 --> 00:05:34.088
I knew you guys would end up like this.

00:05:34.171 --> 00:05:36.922
Why did she follow him to Busan
when her deadline is so close?

00:05:37.130 --> 00:05:38.588
What did she gain from going there?

00:05:38.796 --> 00:05:41.588
Did she go all that way
just to set up a blind date?

00:05:43.047 --> 00:05:44.254
No.

00:05:44.463 --> 00:05:47.421
All energy can be
converted into another form.

00:05:50.296 --> 00:05:52.130
Love, come here.

00:05:52.713 --> 00:05:53.713
Follow me.

00:05:55.338 --> 00:05:58.213
We can use this anxious heart for writing.

00:05:58.922 --> 00:06:01.005
Now, pour it all out.

00:06:02.463 --> 00:06:03.796
No, not here.

00:06:20.254 --> 00:06:21.379
That's right.

00:06:21.463 --> 00:06:23.088
I've got it. It's all coming to me.

00:06:23.671 --> 00:06:25.796
The emotions are just gushing out.

00:06:46.671 --> 00:06:47.671
This is brilliant.

00:06:48.254 --> 00:06:49.254
This is good.

00:06:55.005 --> 00:06:56.671
Am I a genius?

00:07:09.463 --> 00:07:11.755
Yu-mi, guess where I am.

00:07:22.505 --> 00:07:24.338
This looks like my neighborhood.

00:07:28.087 --> 00:07:30.047
THIS LOOKS LIKE MY NEIGHBORHOOD

00:07:30.379 --> 00:07:31.588
That's right.

00:07:31.755 --> 00:07:33.379
I came to your neighborhood.

00:07:33.546 --> 00:07:35.546
I'm supposed to meet Shin Soon-rok here.

00:07:37.671 --> 00:07:39.171
Why did you come all the way here?

00:07:39.254 --> 00:07:40.463
You could have met in Seoul.

00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:43.796
I had work in Ilsan this morning

00:07:44.087 --> 00:07:45.838
so I said it's more convenient here.

00:07:46.379 --> 00:07:48.005
I'll have a good time and report back.

00:07:48.171 --> 00:07:49.796
You don't have to report back.

00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:51.963
No need to report. Have a good...

00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:53.630
He's here.

00:07:53.713 --> 00:07:56.505
YOU DON'T HAVE TO REPORT BACK.
HAVE A GOOD TIME

00:07:57.296 --> 00:07:59.129
He's even more handsome in person.

00:07:59.671 --> 00:08:01.129
I'll contact you later.

00:08:11.171 --> 00:08:12.630
They met.

00:08:12.713 --> 00:08:13.963
They finally met.

00:08:14.046 --> 00:08:15.213
Ignore it.

00:08:15.296 --> 00:08:17.505
I was at my peak concentration.

00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:18.922
Let's keep going.

00:08:23.922 --> 00:08:26.379
But aren't you hungry?

00:08:31.254 --> 00:08:33.254
Hey, Hunger Cell, you're hungry, right?

00:08:34.463 --> 00:08:36.129
How about we eat something first?

00:08:38.296 --> 00:08:40.129
I'm not hungry.

00:08:40.213 --> 00:08:41.963
I ate snacks all night.

00:08:42.046 --> 00:08:43.713
You must be craving sugar.

00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:46.630
I had juice, so I'm not craving it.

00:08:46.713 --> 00:08:48.671
Why not?

00:08:48.755 --> 00:08:50.129
You crave it all the time

00:08:50.213 --> 00:08:51.922
so why not now!

00:08:56.713 --> 00:08:57.755
I'm craving sugar.

00:08:59.546 --> 00:09:00.671
Let's eat something.

00:09:07.588 --> 00:09:08.713
First floor.

00:09:14.713 --> 00:09:16.004
First floor. Cancel.

00:09:16.087 --> 00:09:17.296
Second basement floor.

00:09:17.379 --> 00:09:19.630
What? Aren't we going to
the convenience store?

00:09:26.296 --> 00:09:27.796
How far are you going to go for a snack?

00:09:28.755 --> 00:09:32.630
I'm suddenly craving
strawberry custard bungeoppang.

00:09:33.463 --> 00:09:34.463
Hey, what?

00:09:34.546 --> 00:09:35.588
You're going home

00:09:36.379 --> 00:09:37.379
to buy bungeoppang?

00:09:37.755 --> 00:09:40.463
Oh, this is crazy.
You didn't even bring the car keys...

00:09:44.588 --> 00:09:46.254
Who brought the car keys?

00:09:52.296 --> 00:09:53.838
It's only a ten-minute drive away.

00:09:55.213 --> 00:09:56.671
Let's get some fresh air too.

00:09:58.296 --> 00:10:00.171
I've been pushing myself too hard.

00:10:31.463 --> 00:10:32.463
Oh, my. Wait!

00:10:32.879 --> 00:10:34.546
Isn't that them over there?

00:10:37.838 --> 00:10:39.505
I knew it.

00:10:51.213 --> 00:10:52.379
They really met.

00:10:52.463 --> 00:10:54.129
Of course they met.

00:10:54.213 --> 00:10:55.546
Stop stating the obvious.

00:10:55.879 --> 00:10:57.838
Jennie dressed up nicely today.

00:10:57.921 --> 00:10:59.671
She put a lot of effort
into her makeup too.

00:10:59.755 --> 00:11:01.463
Her curls look great too.

00:11:02.046 --> 00:11:04.087
They look good together.

00:11:04.171 --> 00:11:05.213
Let's go.

00:11:05.296 --> 00:11:06.879
You said you'd finish it today.

00:11:06.962 --> 00:11:08.087
That's right, Yu-mi.

00:11:08.171 --> 00:11:09.921
You might get a parking ticket.

00:11:16.713 --> 00:11:18.379
- What was that?
- What do we do? She saw us.

00:11:19.004 --> 00:11:20.004
Yu-mi.

00:11:28.046 --> 00:11:29.087
Yu-mi!

00:11:33.837 --> 00:11:35.546
What is this? This can't be happening.

00:11:35.630 --> 00:11:38.588
Besides, do you know
Yu-mi didn't even wash her face?

00:11:38.879 --> 00:11:40.671
And her clothes are a mess!

00:11:40.962 --> 00:11:42.671
Let's just go. Let's bolt.

00:11:42.755 --> 00:11:45.046
Everyone, calm down.

00:11:45.171 --> 00:11:47.671
Yu-mi isn't just Kim Yu-mi anymore.

00:11:47.962 --> 00:11:49.795
She's the star writer, Kim Yu-mi.

00:11:50.171 --> 00:11:52.296
We have to protect our writer's pride.

00:11:52.630 --> 00:11:53.837
So what are we supposed to do?

00:11:54.713 --> 00:11:56.087
There's only one thing

00:11:56.379 --> 00:11:58.004
Yu-mi can do now.

00:12:11.505 --> 00:12:13.004
- Jennie.
- Yu-mi!

00:12:13.671 --> 00:12:15.755
- Hello.
- Ms. Kim.

00:12:17.630 --> 00:12:18.671
I was just passing by

00:12:18.755 --> 00:12:21.921
and remembered
the photo you sent, so I peeked.

00:12:22.254 --> 00:12:23.546
To see how it was going.

00:12:24.254 --> 00:12:25.588
But you caught me.

00:12:25.671 --> 00:12:27.588
I thought you were in your studio.

00:12:28.254 --> 00:12:29.713
I came to buy some bungeoppang

00:12:29.795 --> 00:12:31.421
since I only eat from this one place.

00:12:33.588 --> 00:12:35.087
Are you eating something good?

00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:36.962
Yes, pasta.

00:12:37.754 --> 00:12:39.588
- What about you? Did you have lunch?
- Of course I did.

00:12:40.588 --> 00:12:43.129
- I'll let you two get back to it.
- Wait!

00:12:43.671 --> 00:12:44.754
Stay a little longer.

00:12:44.837 --> 00:12:47.171
Hey, I can take a hint.

00:12:47.630 --> 00:12:50.379
But you both look so cool today.

00:12:50.463 --> 00:12:52.505
You don't look like the people I know.

00:12:53.795 --> 00:12:56.671
I always look like this, don't I?

00:12:56.754 --> 00:12:58.630
Oh, yes. You're right.

00:12:58.713 --> 00:13:00.546
Well, have a great time.

00:13:00.630 --> 00:13:01.962
Shin PD, see you at the meeting.

00:13:02.046 --> 00:13:03.046
Oh, okay.

00:13:03.421 --> 00:13:04.630
I'll contact you later.

00:13:05.795 --> 00:13:08.795
I sent her a picture
of this place earlier.

00:13:09.296 --> 00:13:10.505
I guess she saw it passing by.

00:13:10.588 --> 00:13:11.588
I see.

00:13:16.630 --> 00:13:17.837
Just a moment.

00:13:18.754 --> 00:13:19.754
Ms. Kim.

00:13:21.087 --> 00:13:23.421
- Why would you...
- I already paid.

00:13:23.505 --> 00:13:25.296
No, why did you pay for this?

00:13:25.379 --> 00:13:27.795
Well, the matchmaker can treat you.

00:13:28.004 --> 00:13:29.254
I'm the older one.

00:13:29.338 --> 00:13:30.837
That's the only path

00:13:30.921 --> 00:13:32.171
for Yu-mi to take now.

00:13:32.921 --> 00:13:34.213
Being the pretty older girl

00:13:35.213 --> 00:13:36.254
who buys meals.

00:13:36.338 --> 00:13:37.338
PRETTY OLDER GIRL

00:13:38.213 --> 00:13:39.505
Have a great time.

00:13:40.630 --> 00:13:41.671
Wait...

00:13:49.505 --> 00:13:50.837
She paid?

00:13:51.087 --> 00:13:52.129
Yes.

00:13:53.463 --> 00:13:55.754
I shouldn't have sent the picture.
I made her worry.

00:13:56.546 --> 00:13:58.505
I think she came all this way
just to buy us a meal.

00:14:03.795 --> 00:14:05.837
Thanks for the meal.

00:14:09.921 --> 00:14:11.795
She's a really good person.

00:14:12.296 --> 00:14:13.421
She's great to work with, right?

00:14:14.046 --> 00:14:15.046
Yes.

00:14:16.795 --> 00:14:19.004
Right, I'm glad I treated them.

00:14:19.087 --> 00:14:20.463
Since we met anyway.

00:14:21.546 --> 00:14:22.588
Good job.

00:14:23.546 --> 00:14:24.588
Good job.

00:14:25.754 --> 00:14:27.296
The pretty older girl

00:14:27.837 --> 00:14:29.254
who buys meals?

00:14:29.962 --> 00:14:33.921
THE PRETTY OLDER GIRL WHO BUYS MEALS

00:14:35.296 --> 00:14:38.588
So now Yu-mi is the
"pretty older girl who buys food"?

00:14:39.171 --> 00:14:41.046
It was an unavoidable situation.

00:14:41.296 --> 00:14:44.004
Still, it was handled well
without making it awkward.

00:14:44.546 --> 00:14:46.921
I didn't wake up just to become

00:14:47.004 --> 00:14:48.879
a "pretty older girl who buys food."

00:14:49.463 --> 00:14:52.712
It's not so bad being the
"pretty older girl who buys food."

00:14:53.296 --> 00:14:56.338
She might just be an
"older girl who buys food."

00:15:04.588 --> 00:15:07.004
PPANGEO PPANGEO

00:15:08.046 --> 00:15:09.921
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

00:15:10.213 --> 00:15:12.463
Ten strawberry custard bungeoppang please.

00:15:12.546 --> 00:15:13.546
Okay.

00:15:13.837 --> 00:15:16.171
But it will be about five minutes.

00:15:16.254 --> 00:15:17.879
- Oh, that's fine.
- Okay.

00:15:17.962 --> 00:15:19.004
I'll pay first.

00:15:21.670 --> 00:15:22.921
Okay, here you go.

00:15:24.921 --> 00:15:25.921
By the way...

00:15:26.712 --> 00:15:27.921
Are you sick?

00:15:28.879 --> 00:15:29.879
Me, sick?

00:15:30.087 --> 00:15:32.171
- I'm not.
- Well...

00:15:32.379 --> 00:15:34.670
You look a little tired today.

00:15:35.171 --> 00:15:36.296
I see.

00:15:36.795 --> 00:15:38.421
Oh, it shows.

00:15:39.379 --> 00:15:41.171
- I've been swamped with work lately.
- I see.

00:15:42.629 --> 00:15:44.837
I told you we should've put on makeup.

00:15:44.921 --> 00:15:47.795
"Tired" is just a nice way of saying
she looks like a mess.

00:16:04.795 --> 00:16:06.629
Thank you for the meal.

00:16:07.213 --> 00:16:08.712
Thank you so much!

00:16:08.837 --> 00:16:11.296
For a handsome man
and a delicious lunch. Hehe.

00:16:12.545 --> 00:16:13.712
You're the best!

00:16:17.379 --> 00:16:18.463
As you age

00:16:18.545 --> 00:16:21.795
you need more excuses
to protect your pride.

00:16:29.837 --> 00:16:32.587
Maybe that's why there are so many

00:16:33.213 --> 00:16:34.879
"pretty older girls who buy meals."

00:16:46.338 --> 00:16:48.837
EPISODE 17
THE CHARM OF THE GAME

00:16:59.421 --> 00:17:00.421
It's Jennie.

00:17:00.795 --> 00:17:01.879
Jennie.

00:17:02.962 --> 00:17:04.213
Are you really reporting back?

00:17:04.296 --> 00:17:05.421
Don't answer it!

00:17:05.712 --> 00:17:07.004
I'll call her after I finish.

00:17:07.087 --> 00:17:08.504
Hey!

00:17:08.587 --> 00:17:10.004
How can you not answer?

00:17:18.670 --> 00:17:19.670
Hey, Jennie.

00:17:20.129 --> 00:17:21.921
Are you in your studio?

00:17:22.379 --> 00:17:23.421
Yeah, in my studio.

00:17:24.421 --> 00:17:25.921
Did it go well...

00:17:26.254 --> 00:17:27.629
I'm nearby right now.

00:17:27.921 --> 00:17:29.129
Can I come up for a bit?

00:17:30.754 --> 00:17:32.879
- Here?
- I have something to give you.

00:17:34.795 --> 00:17:37.338
- Sure.
- What was the unit number again?

00:17:37.795 --> 00:17:38.879
It's 1505.

00:17:39.462 --> 00:17:40.962
Okay, see you soon.

00:17:41.629 --> 00:17:42.629
Okay.

00:17:50.462 --> 00:17:52.004
She's coming up right away?

00:17:56.754 --> 00:17:58.754
- Yu-mi.
- Jennie, come in.

00:18:00.462 --> 00:18:02.338
You've been busy lately, right?

00:18:02.462 --> 00:18:05.504
Soon-rok said you'd be very busy
since your deadline is tomorrow.

00:18:06.087 --> 00:18:07.545
Soon-rok?

00:18:07.629 --> 00:18:09.629
They're on a first name basis already?

00:18:09.712 --> 00:18:12.296
Isn't that better
than calling each other by nicknames?

00:18:14.921 --> 00:18:16.171
I am busy...

00:18:16.296 --> 00:18:18.462
but I have a deadline every week

00:18:18.545 --> 00:18:19.587
so I'm fine.

00:18:20.338 --> 00:18:21.338
Well...

00:18:21.420 --> 00:18:23.587
I just wanted to give you this.

00:18:23.921 --> 00:18:24.921
What's this?

00:18:25.087 --> 00:18:26.129
They're cookies.

00:18:26.213 --> 00:18:28.046
For a sugar boost
when you're stuck with work.

00:18:28.129 --> 00:18:30.462
Gosh, you shouldn't have.

00:18:31.129 --> 00:18:32.670
Sit down. Want some tea?

00:18:33.046 --> 00:18:34.046
Can I?

00:18:34.129 --> 00:18:35.171
Of course, you can.

00:18:39.296 --> 00:18:41.379
I feel this every time I come here

00:18:41.629 --> 00:18:43.379
but the view here is really amazing.

00:18:43.754 --> 00:18:44.754
Right?

00:18:44.879 --> 00:18:46.712
I can't move because of the view.

00:18:48.545 --> 00:18:50.171
So, how did it go?

00:18:50.962 --> 00:18:51.962
The date?

00:18:54.046 --> 00:18:55.046
Yeah.

00:18:55.420 --> 00:18:56.420
How was it?

00:19:01.254 --> 00:19:03.087
Can I be honest?

00:19:04.338 --> 00:19:05.670
I guess it was a bust.

00:19:05.754 --> 00:19:06.795
Of course.

00:19:06.879 --> 00:19:09.338
- So you didn't like him?
- I like him.

00:19:10.712 --> 00:19:11.795
You like him?

00:19:16.587 --> 00:19:17.795
He's totally my type.

00:19:18.670 --> 00:19:20.462
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

00:19:21.296 --> 00:19:25.378
At first, I thought he seemed a bit cold

00:19:26.171 --> 00:19:28.587
but the way
he smiled sometimes was so cute.

00:19:29.670 --> 00:19:32.171
I know. I know what you mean.

00:19:32.378 --> 00:19:34.462
And he was surprisingly funny.

00:19:34.754 --> 00:19:36.921
He's a bit quirky,
like he's in his own little world.

00:19:37.504 --> 00:19:38.754
I told you

00:19:39.087 --> 00:19:40.462
I know what you mean.

00:19:41.171 --> 00:19:42.795
I'm glad you liked him.

00:19:43.795 --> 00:19:44.795
But I'm not sure

00:19:44.879 --> 00:19:48.545
what Soon-rok thinks of me.

00:19:49.462 --> 00:19:52.337
- Why?
- We said bye on a good note

00:19:53.504 --> 00:19:55.337
but I feel he won't contact me.

00:19:55.837 --> 00:19:57.213
I'm not sure.

00:19:57.296 --> 00:19:58.420
You should do it.

00:19:59.879 --> 00:20:00.962
Yu-mi.

00:20:02.712 --> 00:20:05.129
Can't you ask him for me?

00:20:06.046 --> 00:20:07.337
- Me?
- Yes.

00:20:07.795 --> 00:20:09.378
Can't you just casually ask him

00:20:09.754 --> 00:20:11.420
what he thinks of me?

00:20:14.587 --> 00:20:17.504
I set you up and bought you a meal.
Isn't that enough?

00:20:17.837 --> 00:20:19.254
Do I have to provide
after-sales service too?

00:20:20.213 --> 00:20:21.504
And whose fault is this?

00:20:21.795 --> 00:20:24.962
Who came up with the "pretty older girl
who buys meals" concept?

00:20:29.921 --> 00:20:30.921
Fine.

00:20:31.004 --> 00:20:32.545
- I'll ask him later...
- Now.

00:20:34.129 --> 00:20:35.921
Can you ask him right now?

00:20:38.129 --> 00:20:39.420
- Now?
- Yes.

00:20:40.171 --> 00:20:42.171
I'm dying to know.

00:21:02.420 --> 00:21:04.004
MS. KIM

00:21:10.087 --> 00:21:11.171
Yes, Ms. Kim.

00:21:11.462 --> 00:21:13.629
Shin PD, is this a good time to talk?

00:21:14.129 --> 00:21:15.129
Yes.

00:21:15.420 --> 00:21:17.253
Oh, have you sent the manuscript?

00:21:17.587 --> 00:21:19.587
I haven't been able to check my email yet.

00:21:19.670 --> 00:21:21.378
No, it's not about that.

00:21:22.378 --> 00:21:24.295
How was it?

00:21:25.504 --> 00:21:26.504
Sorry?

00:21:26.629 --> 00:21:28.504
The date today...

00:21:30.337 --> 00:21:31.337
Oh, the date.

00:21:32.046 --> 00:21:33.212
I was just curious.

00:21:34.212 --> 00:21:36.462
Well, we met and it went well.

00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:38.295
She seemed like a nice person.

00:21:39.337 --> 00:21:40.378
Right?

00:21:40.462 --> 00:21:42.129
Jennie is so cute, right?

00:21:42.212 --> 00:21:44.378
She's so cheerful and a great person.

00:21:44.462 --> 00:21:46.087
She's a total mood-maker.

00:21:47.295 --> 00:21:49.295
Yes. I think so.

00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:52.462
So...

00:21:55.295 --> 00:21:56.587
Well...

00:21:57.087 --> 00:21:58.212
you're going to

00:21:58.962 --> 00:22:00.337
see her again, right?

00:22:03.545 --> 00:22:04.545
Oh, yes.

00:22:05.253 --> 00:22:06.504
- Really?
- Yes.

00:22:07.004 --> 00:22:08.295
I should contact her.

00:22:08.837 --> 00:22:10.171
Oh, yes. Right.

00:22:10.420 --> 00:22:11.795
That's great.

00:22:11.879 --> 00:22:15.046
Okay, I'll let you know
when I send the manuscript.

00:22:16.420 --> 00:22:17.420
Okay.

00:22:20.629 --> 00:22:21.712
Shin PD said

00:22:22.462 --> 00:22:24.754
he had a lot of fun too.
He said it was fun.

00:22:24.837 --> 00:22:25.879
Really?

00:22:27.046 --> 00:22:28.170
I bet he'll contact you soon.

00:22:29.587 --> 00:22:31.462
Yu-mi, thank you so much.

00:22:31.545 --> 00:22:33.670
I was so lonely.

00:22:36.462 --> 00:22:38.129
I'm way lonelier.

00:22:38.921 --> 00:22:40.087
- What?
- Nothing.

00:22:45.587 --> 00:22:46.629
Wait.

00:22:49.545 --> 00:22:50.712
Something's wrong.

00:22:58.337 --> 00:23:01.337
Hello? Hey, Love Cell,
something is a bit strange.

00:23:02.295 --> 00:23:04.212
Did you make a misdiagnosis?

00:23:04.378 --> 00:23:07.337
Writer Yu-mi doesn't seem
interested at all.

00:23:07.795 --> 00:23:09.962
Hey, has my diagnosis ever been wrong?

00:23:10.253 --> 00:23:12.462
I'm the authority in this field!

00:23:12.587 --> 00:23:15.504
Look, she set him up
on a blind date right away

00:23:15.587 --> 00:23:16.879
bought him a meal

00:23:16.962 --> 00:23:18.712
and even called him to wish him well.

00:23:18.795 --> 00:23:20.545
What if he drew the line for no reason?

00:23:20.629 --> 00:23:22.087
It's not for no reason.

00:23:22.295 --> 00:23:24.629
He drew a line, she lost interest.

00:23:24.712 --> 00:23:26.170
Is that it?

00:23:26.253 --> 00:23:28.128
Well, isn't that a relief anyway?

00:23:28.378 --> 00:23:29.504
We have to work together

00:23:29.587 --> 00:23:30.921
so it's a relief.

00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:33.962
It is a relief...

00:23:35.462 --> 00:23:36.837
Is it really a relief?

00:23:40.587 --> 00:23:42.420
Then why do I feel bad?

00:23:43.629 --> 00:23:44.629
Me?

00:23:44.921 --> 00:23:46.086
I don't feel bad.

00:23:47.086 --> 00:23:48.754
Right? I don't, right?

00:23:49.337 --> 00:23:50.378
I'm just tired.

00:23:50.462 --> 00:23:52.837
Right, it's because you're tired.

00:24:00.962 --> 00:24:03.420
PRIME LOVE CELL

00:24:27.212 --> 00:24:28.545
Hello.

00:24:28.879 --> 00:24:29.962
You're here.

00:24:30.504 --> 00:24:32.712
I thought you were coming with Jang PD.

00:24:33.212 --> 00:24:36.253
- I'm coming from another meeting.
- I see.

00:24:36.712 --> 00:24:37.754
Would you like some coffee?

00:24:38.712 --> 00:24:40.295
Could I have an iced Americano?

00:24:40.587 --> 00:24:42.295
- Of course.
- Thank you.

00:24:48.128 --> 00:24:49.253
The script was interesting.

00:24:50.629 --> 00:24:52.295
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

00:24:52.837 --> 00:24:56.004
This episode's emotional scenes
were especially good.

00:24:57.962 --> 00:24:58.962
That's a relief.

00:24:59.462 --> 00:25:02.045
If you say it's good,
then it must be really good.

00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:05.754
You're not the type to say things
just to make a writer feel good.

00:25:07.962 --> 00:25:09.170
Is that the image I have?

00:25:10.587 --> 00:25:11.795
It's not an image.

00:25:12.253 --> 00:25:13.378
You're that kind of person.

00:25:13.795 --> 00:25:14.795
Aren't you?

00:25:15.670 --> 00:25:16.670
Oh, I see.

00:25:17.587 --> 00:25:19.003
So that's the kind of person I am.

00:25:20.837 --> 00:25:22.253
There are a few minor things

00:25:22.337 --> 00:25:24.212
but I'll mention them at the meeting.

00:25:25.170 --> 00:25:26.212
Okay.

00:25:35.670 --> 00:25:36.837
Yu-mi.

00:25:36.921 --> 00:25:38.504
You said you have a meeting today, right?

00:25:38.879 --> 00:25:40.086
Did Soon-rok get there?

00:25:40.921 --> 00:25:42.212
I'm just curious.

00:25:42.795 --> 00:25:44.754
I haven't heard from him yet.

00:25:48.879 --> 00:25:49.921
By the way...

00:25:52.462 --> 00:25:53.754
Did you contact...

00:25:57.003 --> 00:25:58.045
Jennie?

00:25:59.545 --> 00:26:00.587
Oh, right.

00:26:01.504 --> 00:26:02.504
Not yet.

00:26:04.754 --> 00:26:05.754
Okay.

00:26:14.545 --> 00:26:15.545
Do I...

00:26:16.879 --> 00:26:17.961
really have to?

00:26:20.212 --> 00:26:21.378
Oh, no.

00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:24.378
Of course not.

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:26.420
Okay.

00:26:26.670 --> 00:26:27.837
I'll contact her soon.

00:26:30.420 --> 00:26:31.420
What was that?

00:26:31.545 --> 00:26:32.920
Why the grim face?

00:26:33.253 --> 00:26:34.295
Don't jump to conclusions.

00:26:34.378 --> 00:26:35.754
It's the same as usual.

00:27:15.837 --> 00:27:17.754
- Ms. Kim, I'm here.
- You're here.

00:27:17.837 --> 00:27:19.420
You two came together?

00:27:19.837 --> 00:27:22.295
- Hello.
- We ran into each other on the way.

00:27:22.878 --> 00:27:24.462
Shin PD, hello.

00:27:24.545 --> 00:27:26.920
- Shin PD, you're here already?
- Hello.

00:28:05.712 --> 00:28:07.170
JENNIE

00:28:07.253 --> 00:28:09.253
Yu-mi, I heard from Soon-rok.

00:28:10.878 --> 00:28:13.253
We're meeting on Friday. Yay!

00:28:15.295 --> 00:28:16.337
That's great.

00:28:17.587 --> 00:28:19.337
I'll do my best. Let's go!

00:28:25.128 --> 00:28:27.253
Right, I feel relieved.

00:28:27.337 --> 00:28:29.045
I've done all I can.

00:28:29.128 --> 00:28:30.253
Let's just forget about it.

00:28:30.629 --> 00:28:32.378
You guys handle it yourselves.

00:28:32.462 --> 00:28:33.920
Just stop already, please.

00:28:59.504 --> 00:29:00.670
What should I make?

00:29:14.086 --> 00:29:16.712
Player Seo Hyeong-jun has come out.
He has one win, one loss, four holds.

00:29:16.794 --> 00:29:20.920
An ERA of 2.33 and a HIP of 1.93.

00:29:21.920 --> 00:29:24.045
Player Seo Hyeong-jun's
curveball was really good

00:29:24.128 --> 00:29:27.545
but in the end,
KT's offense didn't explode

00:29:27.794 --> 00:29:30.794
- so he was pulled with no decision.
- Yes.

00:29:32.003 --> 00:29:34.086
Jang Jin-hyeok comes in
as the center fielder

00:29:34.170 --> 00:29:37.587
and Player Kwon Dong-jin
comes in as the shortstop.

00:29:39.545 --> 00:29:43.629
It looks like the first tag
touched the ground first.

00:29:44.086 --> 00:29:45.961
- To the side.
- It touched and then grazed past.

00:29:46.045 --> 00:29:47.629
- So it happened in two motions.
- Yes.

00:29:47.712 --> 00:29:49.170
Not in a single motion.

00:29:51.753 --> 00:29:53.212
Sliding to the side...

00:29:53.295 --> 00:29:56.420
The wall, the wall, it's over.

00:29:58.253 --> 00:30:01.337
He catches it there
and creates a deflected hit.

00:30:04.545 --> 00:30:06.753
LOHAS is coming alive like this.

00:30:08.420 --> 00:30:10.045
First score, KT Wiz.

00:30:12.878 --> 00:30:14.794
Both left and right-handed
batters are swinging

00:30:14.878 --> 00:30:17.462
but he's weaker from the right...

00:30:17.545 --> 00:30:19.587
But something's off.

00:30:19.794 --> 00:30:21.337
Since his batting is improving

00:30:21.420 --> 00:30:24.337
he's hitting homers from the right.

00:30:24.920 --> 00:30:29.629
In this game, his son pitched,
and he's coming to bat now....

00:30:32.253 --> 00:30:34.295
- Heave, ho, heave, ho.
- Heave, ho, heave, ho.

00:30:34.378 --> 00:30:35.794
- Heave, ho, heave, ho.
- Heave, ho, heave, ho.

00:30:35.878 --> 00:30:37.128
It's strange.

00:30:37.212 --> 00:30:40.462
I'm home, but why don't I feel
like I'm recharging?

00:30:47.128 --> 00:30:49.086
I'm going to sleep more.

00:30:54.545 --> 00:30:57.545
- Hello?
- Hey, you did something useless.

00:30:58.753 --> 00:31:00.753
That stupid moderation surgery.

00:31:00.878 --> 00:31:03.003
I shouldn't have brought up
the blind date.

00:31:03.295 --> 00:31:06.378
I drew a line to avoid complications

00:31:06.462 --> 00:31:08.170
but now it's even more complicated.

00:31:08.462 --> 00:31:10.378
I came home, but I can't recharge.

00:31:10.462 --> 00:31:11.961
My head is a mess.

00:31:13.420 --> 00:31:15.295
No, if you're too tired

00:31:15.378 --> 00:31:16.628
you might not be able to recharge.

00:31:16.711 --> 00:31:18.794
No! It's because the surgery went wrong.

00:31:18.878 --> 00:31:21.170
What are you going to do now?

00:31:21.920 --> 00:31:24.420
This is LOHAS showing us.

00:31:24.504 --> 00:31:26.961
- Leaving behind good results.
- Yes.

00:31:34.295 --> 00:31:35.462
Kia is taking the lead.

00:31:35.545 --> 00:31:37.711
WRITER BAEK NA-HEE

00:31:44.669 --> 00:31:45.711
Hello?

00:31:46.212 --> 00:31:48.086
Shin PD, are you free to talk?

00:31:48.587 --> 00:31:49.587
Yes.

00:31:49.753 --> 00:31:52.545
Since our male lead likes games

00:31:52.628 --> 00:31:55.711
Ms. Kim ordered a game console
to try it out herself.

00:31:55.794 --> 00:31:57.337
It arrived a little while ago.

00:31:57.794 --> 00:31:59.045
Oh, really?

00:31:59.586 --> 00:32:03.295
I thought the installation
would be simple, so I said I'd do it

00:32:03.378 --> 00:32:04.920
but I just can't seem to do it.

00:32:05.462 --> 00:32:07.295
You said you have the same one
at home, right?

00:32:08.295 --> 00:32:09.586
Yes, that's right.

00:32:09.878 --> 00:32:11.212
Just leave it.

00:32:11.420 --> 00:32:12.961
I'll set it up next time I go.

00:32:13.504 --> 00:32:16.045
Okay, so I'm giving up and going home now.

00:32:16.128 --> 00:32:18.128
I'll just put it aside for now.

00:32:18.295 --> 00:32:19.920
Shouldn't Ms. Kim...

00:32:21.086 --> 00:32:22.628
try it out soon?

00:32:23.128 --> 00:32:24.920
Well, I was waiting

00:32:25.003 --> 00:32:27.253
- until Friday...
- Should I go now?

00:32:27.462 --> 00:32:28.462
What?

00:32:28.545 --> 00:32:30.878
Leave it and tell me the studio code.

00:32:30.961 --> 00:32:32.504
I'll go set it up and come back.

00:32:35.003 --> 00:32:36.003
But it's late.

00:32:36.170 --> 00:32:37.711
I don't have anything better to do.

00:32:39.128 --> 00:32:40.128
You just got home

00:32:40.295 --> 00:32:41.420
and you're going out again?

00:32:41.628 --> 00:32:43.836
I'm not charging anyway.

00:32:44.003 --> 00:32:45.753
Though I don't know why.

00:33:05.961 --> 00:33:09.337
I'd rather tire myself out physically
so I can sleep.

00:33:10.462 --> 00:33:12.378
Starting navigation.

00:34:18.628 --> 00:34:19.628
It's done.

00:34:33.003 --> 00:34:34.045
Ms. Kim.

00:34:36.128 --> 00:34:37.337
Wait, what's going on?

00:34:37.669 --> 00:34:39.628
Why'd Writer Yu-mi suddenly show up?

00:34:40.045 --> 00:34:42.420
What do we do?
It's about to run out of battery.

00:34:42.503 --> 00:34:46.337
- Soon-rok, get a grip.
- Get a grip!

00:34:48.586 --> 00:34:49.920
- Why are you here at this hour?
- Why are you...

00:34:52.378 --> 00:34:54.003
I came to set this up.

00:34:54.337 --> 00:34:56.337
Na-hee contacted me
and said she couldn't do it.

00:34:56.628 --> 00:34:57.753
Gosh.

00:34:57.836 --> 00:35:00.295
You didn't have to rush over to do that.

00:35:00.836 --> 00:35:02.628
I didn't have much else to do.

00:35:03.003 --> 00:35:04.337
But Ms. Kim, why are you...

00:35:05.419 --> 00:35:06.544
Oh, me?

00:35:09.586 --> 00:35:10.961
I couldn't sleep

00:35:11.628 --> 00:35:13.045
and didn't want to waste time

00:35:13.128 --> 00:35:15.003
so I thought I'd write
a bit of episode 16.

00:35:16.212 --> 00:35:18.086
But you really startled me.

00:35:19.878 --> 00:35:21.711
I'm almost done.
If you give me ten minutes...

00:35:21.794 --> 00:35:24.170
Don't worry about it.
I don't have to write right now.

00:35:25.086 --> 00:35:26.086
I'll be done soon.

00:35:39.212 --> 00:35:41.628
I brought some
strawberry custard bungeoppang.

00:35:43.045 --> 00:35:44.128
Would you like some?

00:35:44.544 --> 00:35:45.753
Yes, I'll have some.

00:35:47.045 --> 00:35:48.045
Something to drink?

00:35:48.337 --> 00:35:49.878
I have milk

00:35:50.461 --> 00:35:51.461
or cola.

00:35:52.337 --> 00:35:53.337
I'll have milk.

00:35:54.295 --> 00:35:55.586
You have good taste, right?

00:35:55.961 --> 00:35:57.295
Milk is a must with the bungeoppang.

00:35:58.128 --> 00:36:00.628
I was a bit taken aback
when you offered cola for a second.

00:36:08.794 --> 00:36:09.794
Here you go.

00:36:10.586 --> 00:36:11.628
Thank you.

00:36:12.669 --> 00:36:13.669
Would you like to...

00:36:13.794 --> 00:36:15.086
sit here for a moment?

00:36:16.336 --> 00:36:17.377
Me?

00:36:19.003 --> 00:36:20.669
Have you ever used one of these?

00:36:21.461 --> 00:36:24.669
Oh, no. I'm terrible at games.

00:36:24.961 --> 00:36:26.170
I'll give you a quick tutorial.

00:36:26.544 --> 00:36:27.544
Have a seat.

00:36:29.086 --> 00:36:30.544
Oh, okay.

00:36:34.295 --> 00:36:36.461
You have to control everything with this.

00:36:36.920 --> 00:36:38.212
I've seen this a lot.

00:36:39.128 --> 00:36:40.711
It'll be a bit confusing
for the first few days.

00:36:41.628 --> 00:36:45.003
First, place your hands like this.

00:36:46.212 --> 00:36:47.753
Thumbs too.

00:36:47.920 --> 00:36:49.461
Yes, like this.

00:36:51.336 --> 00:36:53.753
See the X and O buttons here?

00:36:54.128 --> 00:36:55.212
Yes.

00:36:55.294 --> 00:36:56.419
O is the back button

00:36:56.503 --> 00:36:58.045
and X is the start button.

00:36:58.253 --> 00:36:59.253
Okay.

00:36:59.544 --> 00:37:01.294
Want to give it a try?

00:37:02.711 --> 00:37:03.711
Start.

00:37:04.128 --> 00:37:07.128
- No, you have to press X.
- Oh, right. X.

00:37:07.586 --> 00:37:08.586
Yes.

00:37:08.669 --> 00:37:09.669
SELECT CHAPTER
SELECT CHARACTER

00:37:13.628 --> 00:37:15.544
See? It's starting, right?

00:37:15.753 --> 00:37:18.753
- Oh, so this is how it starts.
- You did great.

00:37:19.003 --> 00:37:20.212
Okay, now let's learn

00:37:20.294 --> 00:37:21.628
how to move forward and jump.

00:37:21.711 --> 00:37:23.586
Push the left stick up

00:37:24.170 --> 00:37:26.336
while pressing X twice
with your right hand

00:37:26.753 --> 00:37:28.003
then square once, quickly.

00:37:28.294 --> 00:37:29.294
Can you try that?

00:37:31.628 --> 00:37:33.753
- No, not like that...
- Oh, wait...

00:37:34.711 --> 00:37:35.753
Like this.

00:37:36.170 --> 00:37:37.170
Oh, okay.

00:37:37.461 --> 00:37:38.461
Like this.

00:37:40.128 --> 00:37:41.711
No, that's not it.

00:37:43.212 --> 00:37:44.252
Hold on.

00:37:45.711 --> 00:37:48.419
Push the stick up with your left hand

00:37:48.503 --> 00:37:50.461
and press X twice.

00:37:54.920 --> 00:37:56.753
Square button

00:37:56.836 --> 00:37:58.128
and then it does this.

00:37:59.170 --> 00:38:00.753
Like this. See?

00:38:02.669 --> 00:38:04.419
Do you get how to control it?

00:38:20.252 --> 00:38:22.252
You get it, right? How it works?

00:38:23.753 --> 00:38:25.628
Yes, I think I get it...

00:38:26.086 --> 00:38:28.461
but I think I need to practice a bit.

00:38:29.461 --> 00:38:30.461
Yes.

00:38:30.544 --> 00:38:32.836
It'll take a few days to get used to it.

00:38:32.920 --> 00:38:35.336
- Okay. I'll try it by myself.
- Okay.

00:38:48.003 --> 00:38:49.003
Is that not it?

00:38:50.003 --> 00:38:51.211
- What's wrong with it?
- No, slowly.

00:38:51.294 --> 00:38:52.961
Oh, slowly?

00:38:56.669 --> 00:38:57.794
Oh, I got it.

00:38:57.878 --> 00:38:58.878
Or not?

00:39:03.128 --> 00:39:05.294
- Why is it doing this?
- No, while moving forward.

00:39:05.377 --> 00:39:06.878
Yes, like this?

00:39:07.503 --> 00:39:08.544
Hold on.

00:39:19.086 --> 00:39:20.086
Oh, gosh.

00:39:48.211 --> 00:39:49.336
Like... like this.

00:39:50.211 --> 00:39:51.753
Oh, okay, okay.

00:39:51.836 --> 00:39:53.961
I totally get it now. It's like this.

00:39:54.920 --> 00:39:56.920
How do I... I'll try it myself.

00:39:57.711 --> 00:39:58.711
Oh, okay.

00:40:12.252 --> 00:40:13.252
Oh, I got it.

00:40:15.377 --> 00:40:16.711
Gosh, this is simple.

00:40:16.794 --> 00:40:18.003
You're good at this.

00:40:19.419 --> 00:40:20.753
Do you want to try another game?

00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:23.127
- Right now?
- Yes.

00:40:23.211 --> 00:40:24.294
Which one is fun?

00:40:24.461 --> 00:40:25.461
One moment.

00:40:32.753 --> 00:40:33.920
Oh, this one is fun.

00:40:34.003 --> 00:40:35.628
This one's super popular.

00:40:35.711 --> 00:40:37.461
It's a game even a complete
beginner can play.

00:40:37.544 --> 00:40:38.544
I recommend it.

00:40:38.920 --> 00:40:39.920
Another one?

00:40:40.336 --> 00:40:43.419
Oh, this one is a game with a story

00:40:43.503 --> 00:40:45.085
so I'm sure you'll like it, Ms. Kim.

00:40:45.336 --> 00:40:46.669
This one is really good.

00:40:46.753 --> 00:40:47.753
It's...

00:40:47.836 --> 00:40:48.961
But, Shin PD...

00:40:49.920 --> 00:40:52.252
It's late. Shouldn't you be going?

00:40:54.544 --> 00:40:56.045
It's already past twelve o'clock.

00:40:58.503 --> 00:40:59.544
Is it...

00:41:01.920 --> 00:41:03.211
You're right.

00:41:05.127 --> 00:41:06.628
I'll try it by myself.

00:41:06.878 --> 00:41:08.711
I'll get the hang of it if I keep playing.

00:41:09.211 --> 00:41:11.003
Okay. Take your time.

00:41:12.669 --> 00:41:13.753
Thanks for coming so late.

00:41:14.294 --> 00:41:15.294
It's nothing.

00:41:16.461 --> 00:41:18.711
Then I'll be going now.

00:41:18.794 --> 00:41:19.961
Okay.

00:41:20.503 --> 00:41:22.544
- I'll just clean this up then.
- Oh, no, please.

00:41:22.628 --> 00:41:23.836
I'll clean it up.

00:41:24.461 --> 00:41:26.586
Then I'll just take the box out.

00:41:40.127 --> 00:41:41.211
Thank you.

00:41:41.586 --> 00:41:42.669
It's nothing.

00:41:42.961 --> 00:41:43.961
Call me anytime

00:41:44.127 --> 00:41:45.252
if you have trouble.

00:41:46.294 --> 00:41:48.252
I have to try it myself.
I won't bother you.

00:41:48.836 --> 00:41:49.836
It's not a bother.

00:41:52.211 --> 00:41:54.127
Okay. If I really can't do it

00:41:54.377 --> 00:41:55.377
I'll call you.

00:41:55.961 --> 00:41:57.002
Okay.

00:42:06.211 --> 00:42:08.002
- Bye.
- Going down.

00:42:08.836 --> 00:42:09.878
Take care.

00:42:09.961 --> 00:42:11.628
Door closing.

00:42:27.377 --> 00:42:28.503
It's so late.

00:42:31.252 --> 00:42:32.711
I'm already tired

00:42:32.794 --> 00:42:34.753
and I couldn't even charge...

00:42:41.836 --> 00:42:42.836
What's this?

00:42:42.920 --> 00:42:45.294
This isn't my house,
so why are the lights so bright?

00:43:36.753 --> 00:43:41.669
EPISODE 18 VINTAGE WINE

00:43:44.960 --> 00:43:45.960
Where are you going?

00:43:47.419 --> 00:43:48.711
I'm going to a meeting.

00:43:48.960 --> 00:43:50.586
- A meeting with Yu-mi's team?
- Yes.

00:43:51.461 --> 00:43:53.169
- Why?
- If you go now, when will it end?

00:43:53.753 --> 00:43:54.877
I don't know.

00:43:55.169 --> 00:43:57.211
- In two or three hours?
- You'll have dinner too?

00:43:57.377 --> 00:43:59.127
Well, it'll probably end before that.

00:43:59.461 --> 00:44:00.960
- But why...
- It's nothing.

00:44:01.211 --> 00:44:02.586
Do well. Good luck.

00:44:18.919 --> 00:44:20.877
Soon-rok, are you busy?

00:44:21.753 --> 00:44:23.753
Where are we meeting today?

00:44:24.669 --> 00:44:27.753
Oh, no. He forgot to make a reservation
at the restaurant.

00:44:27.877 --> 00:44:29.794
Soon-rok said he'd do it.

00:44:31.835 --> 00:44:35.503
RESTAURANTS

00:44:36.294 --> 00:44:37.960
It's Friday evening.

00:44:38.044 --> 00:44:39.919
We might not be able to get a reservation.

00:44:42.044 --> 00:44:43.211
I'll get going now.

00:44:46.794 --> 00:44:47.794
Yoo PD, I'll be leaving now.

00:44:48.336 --> 00:44:49.669
Yes, goodbye.

00:44:52.377 --> 00:44:54.336
What if we change the username?

00:44:54.711 --> 00:44:56.794
I think the username
makes it more obvious.

00:44:57.377 --> 00:45:00.252
But will that make it plausible?

00:45:00.336 --> 00:45:02.419
I don't think the viewers
will know the difference.

00:45:03.169 --> 00:45:06.002
Wouldn't it be better to have them
change the security company?

00:45:06.461 --> 00:45:07.753
The security company?

00:45:08.127 --> 00:45:09.252
If they change the company

00:45:09.336 --> 00:45:11.002
everything will change anyway.

00:45:11.711 --> 00:45:14.252
And the male lead was on a
business trip, so he didn't know.

00:45:14.793 --> 00:45:16.419
That sounds good.

00:45:16.711 --> 00:45:18.628
But I don't know what all changes

00:45:18.711 --> 00:45:20.711
when you change security companies.

00:45:20.919 --> 00:45:23.085
- Oh, I'll look it up.
- Should I look into it?

00:45:23.544 --> 00:45:25.503
I have a friend who works
at a security company.

00:45:25.586 --> 00:45:28.002
Oh, that would be great.
I don't know anything about that.

00:45:28.085 --> 00:45:29.169
I'll look into it.

00:45:29.628 --> 00:45:30.793
Thank you.

00:45:31.877 --> 00:45:34.085
Then it seems everything is settled.

00:45:34.544 --> 00:45:36.377
Should we wrap up the meeting here?

00:45:36.461 --> 00:45:38.793
- Yes, great work everyone.
- Yes.

00:45:38.877 --> 00:45:40.586
What should we do for dinner?

00:45:40.669 --> 00:45:42.960
- Should we grab a bite before we go?
- Yes, sounds good.

00:45:43.377 --> 00:45:45.711
Oh, I have plans.

00:45:46.127 --> 00:45:47.127
That's right.

00:45:47.211 --> 00:45:48.377
You have plans.

00:45:48.960 --> 00:45:50.960
- Let's just the two of us go eat.
- Okay.

00:45:52.002 --> 00:45:53.503
Shin PD, where are you going?

00:45:54.419 --> 00:45:55.461
Great work today.

00:46:17.586 --> 00:46:18.669
Meeting twice means

00:46:18.752 --> 00:46:20.628
we've fulfilled all the manners.

00:46:20.877 --> 00:46:22.211
Let's wrap it up today.

00:46:38.960 --> 00:46:40.044
Yeah, I just arrived.

00:46:40.127 --> 00:46:41.211
What floor is it?

00:46:41.336 --> 00:46:42.793
The 15th floor. Okay.

00:46:45.752 --> 00:46:47.586
What? It's Writer Ju-ho.

00:46:48.169 --> 00:46:49.377
Why is he here?

00:46:52.211 --> 00:46:53.960
Well, the meeting will end early anyway.

00:47:06.877 --> 00:47:07.877
Who is that?

00:47:08.710 --> 00:47:09.960
Who is it?

00:47:10.044 --> 00:47:12.169
Yes, hello. This is Writer Kim Ju-ho.

00:47:12.586 --> 00:47:14.294
- Ms. Kim.
- Who is it?

00:47:14.544 --> 00:47:16.586
He says he's Writer Kim Ju-ho.

00:47:16.668 --> 00:47:18.127
- Kim Ju-ho?
- Yes.

00:47:19.377 --> 00:47:20.710
- He's downstairs?
- Yes.

00:47:21.169 --> 00:47:22.169
What should I do?

00:47:22.294 --> 00:47:23.336
Wait, what?

00:47:24.835 --> 00:47:25.960
Let him in for now.

00:47:27.419 --> 00:47:28.503
- Hello.
- Oh, yes.

00:47:28.586 --> 00:47:29.586
Come in.

00:47:29.710 --> 00:47:31.085
Ms. Kim, he's here.

00:47:33.085 --> 00:47:34.085
Hello, Ms. Kim.

00:47:34.835 --> 00:47:36.044
Hello.

00:47:37.127 --> 00:47:38.877
Am I interrupting something?

00:47:39.336 --> 00:47:40.668
Or may I come in for a moment?

00:47:41.085 --> 00:47:43.085
- Yes, of course. Come in.
- Thank you.

00:47:48.002 --> 00:47:49.793
Your studio is really nice.

00:47:50.586 --> 00:47:51.835
This studio

00:47:52.211 --> 00:47:53.668
is just like you.

00:47:54.586 --> 00:47:56.252
You were surprised that I came
so suddenly, weren't you?

00:47:57.586 --> 00:47:59.169
Of course, I was surprised.

00:47:59.252 --> 00:48:01.461
You came without any notice.

00:48:02.919 --> 00:48:05.793
I had some business in Ilsan

00:48:06.252 --> 00:48:08.627
and I remembered hearing
that your studio was nearby.

00:48:09.127 --> 00:48:10.461
I asked Dae-yong

00:48:10.960 --> 00:48:12.211
and since you had a meeting today

00:48:12.294 --> 00:48:13.461
I thought you'd be here.

00:48:14.002 --> 00:48:15.877
Oh, I see.

00:48:16.461 --> 00:48:17.461
Oh, and...

00:48:18.085 --> 00:48:19.752
I also came to give you this.

00:48:21.127 --> 00:48:22.710
Is this wine?

00:48:24.127 --> 00:48:26.503
Yes, I just got back
from a short trip to Europe.

00:48:26.835 --> 00:48:28.627
I bought some nice vintage wine

00:48:29.044 --> 00:48:30.960
and you came to mind, Ms. Kim.

00:48:31.419 --> 00:48:33.627
Oh, thank you.

00:48:35.544 --> 00:48:36.544
By any chance

00:48:36.627 --> 00:48:38.002
do you like vintage wine?

00:48:38.627 --> 00:48:40.544
I don't know much about wine.

00:48:40.752 --> 00:48:41.960
I see.

00:48:42.419 --> 00:48:45.752
It's a 1997 vintage.

00:48:47.085 --> 00:48:49.044
A 1997 vintage?

00:48:49.960 --> 00:48:51.544
I bet your assistant

00:48:51.960 --> 00:48:54.169
wasn't born then, right?

00:48:54.503 --> 00:48:56.294
Right, I was born in 1999.

00:48:57.710 --> 00:48:59.793
Ms. Kim, do you happen to remember?

00:48:59.877 --> 00:49:02.377
- In 1997, we...
- I don't remember

00:49:02.461 --> 00:49:05.211
what I did in 1997 at all.

00:49:05.419 --> 00:49:06.793
I was too young.

00:49:07.127 --> 00:49:08.835
I'm not from your generation

00:49:08.919 --> 00:49:10.002
so don't ask me.

00:49:13.002 --> 00:49:14.002
But...

00:49:14.169 --> 00:49:16.461
this seems very expensive.
Why give it to me?

00:49:17.127 --> 00:49:18.127
Well...

00:49:18.585 --> 00:49:20.127
It's a peace offering.

00:49:21.127 --> 00:49:23.169
I felt I was a bit rude in Busan

00:49:24.085 --> 00:49:25.503
so I wanted to apologize.

00:49:28.252 --> 00:49:29.877
If you put it that way

00:49:30.752 --> 00:49:32.543
then I should apologize too.

00:49:33.793 --> 00:49:36.419
I lost my temper that day too.

00:49:36.835 --> 00:49:38.752
So are we even now?

00:49:40.252 --> 00:49:41.543
Well...

00:49:41.627 --> 00:49:43.169
it's not something
we need to be even about.

00:49:43.252 --> 00:49:44.461
It was just an incident.

00:49:45.668 --> 00:49:46.960
I knew it.

00:49:47.169 --> 00:49:49.627
Ms. Kim, you live up to your name.

00:49:50.044 --> 00:49:53.668
But Dae-yong kept pushing me
to come and apologize.

00:49:54.877 --> 00:49:56.461
So you were pressured into coming.

00:49:56.543 --> 00:49:57.585
No wonder.

00:49:58.419 --> 00:50:00.127
Well, anyway...

00:50:01.377 --> 00:50:02.877
let's at least shake hands to make up.

00:50:03.252 --> 00:50:04.294
I'm sorry.

00:50:05.585 --> 00:50:08.668
Well, I'm not sure if this calls
for a handshake...

00:50:08.960 --> 00:50:09.960
But, sure.

00:50:12.419 --> 00:50:14.793
Shouldn't we take a photo as proof?

00:50:14.877 --> 00:50:15.877
So the Chief Editor can see it.

00:50:17.793 --> 00:50:20.710
This is why I like you, Ms. Kim.

00:50:21.627 --> 00:50:23.336
- Have a seat.
- Oh, yes.

00:50:24.336 --> 00:50:25.543
Would you like some coffee?

00:50:26.877 --> 00:50:28.543
You're offering coffee too?

00:50:29.543 --> 00:50:30.960
Of course. What would you like?

00:50:31.044 --> 00:50:32.044
Okay, then...

00:50:32.877 --> 00:50:35.085
I'll have an iced latte, please.

00:50:35.377 --> 00:50:37.085
- Okay.
- Just a moment.

00:50:45.752 --> 00:50:47.294
I don't see Shin PD.

00:50:47.793 --> 00:50:49.627
I heard there was a meeting,
so I thought he would be here too.

00:50:50.585 --> 00:50:52.252
He had an appointment, so he left early.

00:50:52.668 --> 00:50:55.002
You don't think he heard
I was coming and bailed, do you?

00:50:55.668 --> 00:50:57.127
I don't think so.

00:50:57.668 --> 00:50:59.336
Soon-rok is upset with me.

00:50:59.543 --> 00:51:02.460
The rumor is that you're the one
who's upset, Mr. Kim.

00:51:04.169 --> 00:51:05.585
Gosh, no way.

00:51:10.377 --> 00:51:11.502
But I feel more comfortable

00:51:11.835 --> 00:51:13.252
without him.

00:51:13.752 --> 00:51:15.752
He kept acting like your bodyguard.

00:51:18.877 --> 00:51:19.877
What?

00:51:21.002 --> 00:51:22.294
Your meeting is over, right?

00:51:22.919 --> 00:51:24.460
Would you like to have dinner together?

00:51:37.002 --> 00:51:38.502
I just got here.

00:51:41.085 --> 00:51:42.127
I'm here now too.

00:51:55.211 --> 00:51:56.211
Yes, Shin PD.

00:51:56.668 --> 00:51:58.835
Are you still at the studio?

00:51:59.211 --> 00:52:00.627
No, we left.

00:52:02.294 --> 00:52:03.294
Is everything okay?

00:52:03.752 --> 00:52:04.752
What do you mean?

00:52:06.585 --> 00:52:09.376
Has Writer Kim Ju-ho left?

00:52:10.085 --> 00:52:12.002
How did you know he came by?

00:52:13.002 --> 00:52:15.002
- I saw him when I was leaving.
- I see.

00:52:15.085 --> 00:52:17.835
We're having dinner with Writer Kim now.

00:52:19.252 --> 00:52:20.668
- Dinner?
- Yes.

00:52:20.919 --> 00:52:23.585
Mr. Kim brought some vintage wine

00:52:23.835 --> 00:52:25.169
and he suggested we open it together

00:52:25.252 --> 00:52:26.543
so we came to Roti Vino.

00:52:26.627 --> 00:52:28.418
And it's really delicious.

00:52:28.502 --> 00:52:32.294
Mr. Kim explained the wine so well.

00:52:32.376 --> 00:52:33.418
Okay, I get it.

00:52:34.418 --> 00:52:36.252
- Enjoy your dinner.
- Okay.

00:52:36.376 --> 00:52:37.376
Bye.

00:53:16.960 --> 00:53:19.002
Let me give you our menu.

00:53:19.085 --> 00:53:21.169
- Thank you.
- Is this for takeout?

00:53:21.252 --> 00:53:23.585
No, I'll order when my party arrives.

00:53:48.960 --> 00:53:50.085
Here is the wine you ordered.

00:53:54.169 --> 00:53:55.211
What is this?

00:53:55.752 --> 00:53:57.211
The gentleman there ordered it.

00:54:05.252 --> 00:54:06.752
This is already the third bottle.

00:54:07.002 --> 00:54:08.127
Would you like to taste it?

00:54:08.211 --> 00:54:09.960
No, actually.

00:54:10.543 --> 00:54:12.376
Please fill this glass all the way.

00:54:12.460 --> 00:54:14.418
- And just a little for us, please.
- Of course.

00:54:25.418 --> 00:54:26.585
Let me clear the glasses.

00:54:30.169 --> 00:54:31.169
Na-hee.

00:54:31.418 --> 00:54:33.877
We'll leave after this dessert.

00:54:34.376 --> 00:54:35.376
What?

00:54:36.710 --> 00:54:38.335
Go pay before he orders more.

00:54:38.752 --> 00:54:39.877
Oh, okay.

00:54:47.752 --> 00:54:50.877
That guy just doesn't know when to stop.

00:54:52.585 --> 00:54:54.251
Gosh, he always crosses the line.

00:54:54.335 --> 00:54:55.793
I shouldn't have made up with him.

00:55:03.585 --> 00:55:05.877
Yu-mi, I think I got stood up.

00:55:10.169 --> 00:55:11.210
What are you talking about?

00:55:13.877 --> 00:55:15.835
Soon-rok canceled on me.

00:55:15.919 --> 00:55:17.293
Right before we were supposed to meet.

00:55:19.793 --> 00:55:21.251
What? Why all of a sudden?

00:55:21.668 --> 00:55:23.210
It's Luce Vino.

00:55:24.210 --> 00:55:26.335
No, the restaurant's name is Luce Vino.

00:55:26.835 --> 00:55:29.627
Oh, it's next to Kim Yu-mi's studio.
You know the one, right?

00:55:31.044 --> 00:55:32.710
Yes, that place.

00:55:33.169 --> 00:55:34.919
Anyway, I'm here.

00:55:39.752 --> 00:55:41.085
Yeah, just come here for now.

00:55:42.335 --> 00:55:43.752
He canceled right before?

00:55:46.044 --> 00:55:47.044
Yeah.

00:55:47.127 --> 00:55:49.168
I'm eating by myself right now.

00:55:51.127 --> 00:55:54.085
What the heck?

00:55:54.460 --> 00:55:55.502
What was his reason?

00:56:01.793 --> 00:56:03.585
Isn't that Shin PD over there?

00:56:07.585 --> 00:56:08.668
Why is he here?

00:56:11.502 --> 00:56:12.502
I don't know.

00:56:12.585 --> 00:56:13.668
He just said he was sorry.

00:56:19.168 --> 00:56:20.835
Why is he here?

00:56:21.293 --> 00:56:22.293
Okay.

00:56:23.002 --> 00:56:24.002
Okay, I got it.

00:56:27.585 --> 00:56:28.585
Hello, Mr. Kim.

00:56:29.418 --> 00:56:30.418
What is this?

00:56:32.627 --> 00:56:33.668
Why are you out here?

00:56:35.126 --> 00:56:36.668
How did you get here?

00:56:37.418 --> 00:56:39.085
I heard you left early
because you had plans.

00:56:40.293 --> 00:56:41.543
It got canceled.

00:56:42.793 --> 00:56:44.168
I talked to Na-hee

00:56:44.502 --> 00:56:47.210
and she said you were all here, so...

00:56:47.793 --> 00:56:49.168
So I came to see you

00:56:49.460 --> 00:56:51.251
and I also hadn't eaten dinner yet.

00:56:53.418 --> 00:56:54.710
I can still order, right?

00:56:55.335 --> 00:56:56.335
I'm hungry.

00:56:58.585 --> 00:56:59.585
Hey.

00:56:59.835 --> 00:57:00.835
You.

00:57:04.668 --> 00:57:05.752
Are you spying on me?

00:57:07.710 --> 00:57:09.418
Looks like you came to spy on me again.

00:57:09.668 --> 00:57:11.168
The way you suddenly ran here.

00:57:15.293 --> 00:57:18.335
You're seriously driving me crazy.

00:57:22.418 --> 00:57:24.002
What are they talking about?

00:57:24.960 --> 00:57:26.585
I think Mr. Kim is angry.

00:57:27.210 --> 00:57:28.210
I think so too.

00:57:28.293 --> 00:57:29.293
Hey.

00:57:34.919 --> 00:57:35.919
Hey.

00:57:36.126 --> 00:57:38.084
What am I supposed to do with you?

00:57:38.877 --> 00:57:41.793
You've been getting on my nerves
ever since Busan, you jerk.

00:57:46.668 --> 00:57:49.627
Hey, why are you doing this to me?

00:57:49.710 --> 00:57:50.710
Vintage wine.

00:57:50.793 --> 00:57:51.835
Soon-rok, stop.

00:57:52.960 --> 00:57:54.376
What? Vintage wine?

00:57:55.585 --> 00:57:57.543
- What about it?
- The vintage wine...

00:57:59.251 --> 00:58:00.293
has that meaning for you.

00:58:01.418 --> 00:58:05.002
- What does it mean?
- You use vintage wine to woo someone.

00:58:06.627 --> 00:58:08.126
To seduce a woman from work

00:58:08.210 --> 00:58:10.293
you always use the vintage wine.

00:58:10.877 --> 00:58:11.877
Well...

00:58:12.251 --> 00:58:14.919
I think I've seen you do it
to at least five people.

00:58:15.627 --> 00:58:18.418
The last was a baseball team employee
you met during a report, right?

00:58:19.126 --> 00:58:20.251
And the translator.

00:58:20.335 --> 00:58:21.335
Oh, also.

00:58:21.460 --> 00:58:23.543
There was also the Chief Editor
from the Japanese publishing house.

00:58:24.084 --> 00:58:25.835
You always gift them vintage wine

00:58:26.376 --> 00:58:29.293
asking to share memories of that era.

00:58:29.376 --> 00:58:31.251
And it always ended badly.

00:58:32.960 --> 00:58:34.877
You've even pushed me
to clean up your messes.

00:58:38.793 --> 00:58:40.585
Hey, are you really going to
run your mouth like this?

00:58:40.668 --> 00:58:43.251
Yes, stop running your mouth, Soon-rok.

00:58:43.335 --> 00:58:45.960
Chief Editor Ahn doesn't know
about this stuff, does he?

00:58:47.210 --> 00:58:48.835
Because I didn't report it.

00:58:50.293 --> 00:58:52.752
But if he knew about this

00:58:53.293 --> 00:58:55.335
he probably wouldn't try
to set you up with Ms. Kim

00:58:58.668 --> 00:59:00.668
I'm in charge of Ms. Kim right now

00:59:01.418 --> 00:59:03.543
and from the moment you brought

00:59:04.752 --> 00:59:05.752
that damn vintage wine

00:59:05.835 --> 00:59:08.418
I'm in a position
where I can't help but worry.

00:59:16.959 --> 00:59:18.168
Should I go out there?

00:59:19.043 --> 00:59:20.126
Okay.

00:59:20.210 --> 00:59:21.710
Actually, never mind. I'll go.

00:59:27.084 --> 00:59:29.835
Hey, you just hit me?

00:59:30.502 --> 00:59:31.877
This guy actually hits people.

00:59:33.835 --> 00:59:35.418
This son of a bitch. Hey!

00:59:36.251 --> 00:59:37.251
You want to come at me?

00:59:39.043 --> 00:59:40.376
Hey, my glasses!

00:59:50.502 --> 00:59:51.793
I can't believe this. You.

00:59:52.418 --> 00:59:53.418
Hey!

00:59:55.959 --> 00:59:57.710
Let go! Hey, let go!

00:59:57.793 --> 00:59:58.793
What's with them?

01:00:01.251 --> 01:00:03.168
Hey, let go! Let go!

01:00:24.043 --> 01:00:25.710
What are they doing?

01:00:27.668 --> 01:00:28.710
You really...

01:00:31.418 --> 01:00:32.585
Hurry, let's go.

01:00:32.668 --> 01:00:34.126
They must be crazy.

01:00:37.126 --> 01:00:38.293
It looks like a fight broke out.

01:00:47.460 --> 01:00:49.210
I told you to stop, Mr. Kim.

01:00:49.293 --> 01:00:50.543
No, let me go!

01:00:50.627 --> 01:00:52.126
No, really, because...

01:00:52.210 --> 01:00:54.959
Let go! It wasn't me, it was him!

01:00:55.043 --> 01:00:57.835
Let go! Just let go, you jerk!

01:00:57.918 --> 01:00:59.959
- No, I'm telling you it was him.
- What are you doing?

01:01:01.959 --> 01:01:03.210
Jeez, seriously.

01:01:06.251 --> 01:01:08.418
Let go. I'll talk to him. I won't hit him.

01:01:08.502 --> 01:01:09.585
Just let go.

01:01:09.834 --> 01:01:10.876
Jeez.

01:01:12.502 --> 01:01:15.668
- You punk!
- Stop, stop, stop.

01:01:16.001 --> 01:01:18.834
Stop! Stop! Stop!

01:01:18.918 --> 01:01:19.918
Stop.

01:01:22.668 --> 01:01:23.710
That's enough.

01:01:29.752 --> 01:01:31.502
Damn it, let go of me.

01:01:48.710 --> 01:01:50.710
Ms. Kim, please go inside.

01:01:50.876 --> 01:01:53.460
You don't have to worry about it.
I'll handle everything.

01:01:53.543 --> 01:01:54.543
I mean, what was that?

01:01:54.627 --> 01:01:57.084
I have no idea what just happened.

01:01:58.251 --> 01:01:59.876
I know... right?

01:02:00.293 --> 01:02:02.460
But how did you get here?

01:02:04.710 --> 01:02:07.001
I called Ju-ho.

01:02:07.251 --> 01:02:08.876
I told him he should come see you.

01:02:09.126 --> 01:02:11.210
I thought it would be okay
if we all had a meal together...

01:02:11.752 --> 01:02:13.710
- It's all my fault. I'm sorry.
- Jeez.

01:02:14.502 --> 01:02:17.251
You didn't know it would
turn out like this.

01:02:18.376 --> 01:02:19.376
Go on inside.

01:02:19.460 --> 01:02:20.668
I'll contact you later.

01:02:23.918 --> 01:02:25.918
Gosh, I was so surprised.

01:02:26.001 --> 01:02:27.876
I thought I was watching a play.

01:02:27.959 --> 01:02:29.418
The two rushed onto the stage,
then rushed off.

01:02:29.502 --> 01:02:31.043
And they kicked...

01:02:31.126 --> 01:02:32.210
You think this is funny right now?

01:02:32.668 --> 01:02:33.668
I'm sorry.

01:02:35.668 --> 01:02:36.876
Unbelievable.

01:03:42.792 --> 01:03:44.126
We're screwed, Soon-rok.

01:03:44.210 --> 01:03:45.709
We're completely screwed.

01:04:42.168 --> 01:04:43.792
I said we're completely screwed.

01:04:44.502 --> 01:04:46.335
What are you going to do now?

01:04:59.376 --> 01:05:03.210
CHIEF EDITOR AHN DAE-YONG

01:05:14.210 --> 01:05:15.210
Hello?

01:05:15.293 --> 01:05:16.876
Hey, you brat, are you crazy?

01:05:17.168 --> 01:05:18.543
Gosh, this punk.

01:05:18.918 --> 01:05:21.210
I even changed your team,
and you're causing trouble again.

01:05:21.460 --> 01:05:25.001
Hey, who do you think you are,
fighting with a senior writer?

01:05:25.251 --> 01:05:26.251
I...

01:05:26.502 --> 01:05:27.959
didn't do anything.

01:05:28.293 --> 01:05:29.335
Mr. Kim caused this.

01:05:29.418 --> 01:05:31.418
Shut it. Come apologize right now

01:05:31.502 --> 01:05:32.709
or resign.

01:05:33.418 --> 01:05:35.667
I'm at his studio right now,
so get over here immediately.

01:05:36.418 --> 01:05:37.460
I'm sorry.

01:05:38.543 --> 01:05:39.626
But I...

01:05:39.709 --> 01:05:41.918
Don't argue who's right or wrong.

01:05:42.001 --> 01:05:44.043
Settle it later. Apologize first.

01:05:44.293 --> 01:05:45.335
Get over here now.

01:06:24.001 --> 01:06:25.043
Yes, Chief Editor Ahn.

01:06:26.792 --> 01:06:28.084
Yes, yes.

01:06:30.376 --> 01:06:31.876
Then what about Shin PD?

01:06:33.542 --> 01:06:36.084
I told him to come and apologize.
He'll be here soon.

01:06:36.502 --> 01:06:38.335
I have to make them reconcile
today, no matter what.

01:06:38.460 --> 01:06:40.418
But why on earth did they fight?

01:06:41.251 --> 01:06:42.251
I don't know.

01:06:42.335 --> 01:06:43.335
He won't tell me either.

01:06:48.460 --> 01:06:49.460
Okay.

01:06:49.542 --> 01:06:51.168
I'll call you back.

01:06:51.584 --> 01:06:52.959
- Okay, sure.
- Bye.

01:06:55.584 --> 01:06:56.584
Who is it?

01:07:11.501 --> 01:07:12.501
Shin PD.

01:07:14.959 --> 01:07:16.751
I thought you went to see Mr. Kim.

01:07:18.168 --> 01:07:19.335
Why are you here?

01:07:21.501 --> 01:07:23.667
I felt like I had to see you first.

01:07:25.168 --> 01:07:26.168
Why?

01:07:29.501 --> 01:07:30.667
Why did you come here?

01:07:34.251 --> 01:07:35.418
I don't know.

01:07:37.751 --> 01:07:39.210
What do you mean, you don't know?

01:07:42.584 --> 01:07:43.626
I don't know.

01:07:43.959 --> 01:07:45.001
I'm not sure either...

01:07:48.501 --> 01:07:50.626
Why did you break your plans
with Jennie and come here?

01:07:52.210 --> 01:07:53.293
I don't know.

01:07:55.001 --> 01:07:56.667
You don't know that either?

01:07:59.501 --> 01:08:00.918
I shouldn't have done that.

01:08:01.210 --> 01:08:03.168
I know. You shouldn't have.

01:08:11.043 --> 01:08:13.501
So, did you come here
to apologize to me for that?

01:08:16.293 --> 01:08:17.834
It's fine, I'm okay.

01:08:17.918 --> 01:08:20.251
- Just go to...
- I didn't come here to apologize.

01:08:29.918 --> 01:08:30.959
Then why?

01:08:36.043 --> 01:08:37.501
I think...

01:08:44.751 --> 01:08:46.043
I like you.

01:09:27.210 --> 01:09:28.876
PRETTY OLDER GIRL WHO BUYS MEALS

01:09:42.709 --> 01:09:45.334
YUMI'S CELLS 3

01:09:45.417 --> 01:09:48.126
Why is Soon-rok acting
like that right now?

01:09:48.334 --> 01:09:50.667
Everyone, it's a real emergency!

01:09:50.751 --> 01:09:52.334
- I'll take care of it!
- Get him!

01:09:52.417 --> 01:09:54.293
Yu-mi set it up without knowing.

01:09:54.375 --> 01:09:56.626
We already ended things cleanly.

01:09:56.709 --> 01:09:58.667
I'm going to Soon-rok.

01:09:58.751 --> 01:10:01.667
Heart Fever Time!

01:10:01.751 --> 01:10:03.168
Shin PD, come this way.

01:10:03.251 --> 01:10:04.584
Run, Soon-rok!

01:10:07.834 --> 01:10:09.792
Shin PD? What are you doing here?

01:10:10.126 --> 01:10:12.334
It's just like yesterday.